{
  "video_id": "jggHw5PdQV0",
  "title": "How young Africans found a voice on Twitter | Siyanda Mohutsiwa",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12760.0,
      "end_time": 15640.0,
      "text": "It began with one question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17222.0,
      "end_time": 22360.0,
      "text": "If Africa was a bar, what would your country be drinking or doing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 23680.0,
      "end_time": 26456.0,
      "text": "I kicked it off with a guess about South Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 26480.0,
      "end_time": 28536.0,
      "text": "which wasn&#39;t exactly according to the rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28560.0,
      "end_time": 31800.0,
      "text": "because South Africa&#39;s not my country."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31640.0,
      "end_time": 34896.0,
      "text": "But alluding to the country&#39;s continual attempts"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34920.0,
      "end_time": 37256.0,
      "text": "to build a postracial society"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 37280.0,
      "end_time": 40576.0,
      "text": "after being ravaged for decades by apartheid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 40600.0,
      "end_time": 46936.0,
      "text": "I tweeted, #ifafricawasabar South Africa would be drinking all kinds of alcohol"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 46960.0,
      "end_time": 49320.0,
      "text": "and begging them to get along in its stomach."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 50960.0,
      "end_time": 52656.0,
      "text": "And then I waited."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 52680.0,
      "end_time": 56136.0,
      "text": "And then I had that funny feeling where I wondered if I crossed the line."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 56160.0,
      "end_time": 59336.0,
      "text": "So, I sent out a few other tweets about my own country"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 59360.0,
      "end_time": 61920.0,
      "text": "and a few other African countries I&#39;m familiar with."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 62400.0,
      "end_time": 63656.0,
      "text": "And then I waited again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 63680.0,
      "end_time": 65560.0,
      "text": "but this time"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 65800.0,
      "end_time": 68496.0,
      "text": "I read through almost every tweet I had ever tweeted"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 68520.0,
      "end_time": 70256.0,
      "text": "to convince myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 70280.0,
      "end_time": 74376.0,
      "text": "no, to remind myself that I&#39;m really funny"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 74400.0,
      "end_time": 77519.0,
      "text": "and that if nobody gets it, that&#39;s fine."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 78960.0,
      "end_time": 80175.0,
      "text": "But luckily,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 80200.0,
      "end_time": 82416.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t have to do that for very long."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 82440.0,
      "end_time": 85480.0,
      "text": "Very soon, people were participating."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 86280.0,
      "end_time": 89536.0,
      "text": "In fact, by the end of that week in July,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89560.0,
      "end_time": 92960.0,
      "text": "the hashtag #ifafricawasabar"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92120.0,
      "end_time": 95816.0,
      "text": "would have garnered around 60,000 tweets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 95840.0,
      "end_time": 97496.0,
      "text": "lit up the continent"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 97520.0,
      "end_time": 100679.0,
      "text": "and made its way to publications all over the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 101240.0,
      "end_time": 104399.0,
      "text": "People were using the hashtag to do many different things."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 105280.0,
      "end_time": 107456.0,
      "text": "To poke fun at their stereotypes:"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 107480.0,
      "end_time": 110960.0,
      "text": "[#IfAfricaWasABar Nigeria would be outside explaining"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 110120.0,
      "end_time": 111896.0,
      "text": "that he will pay the entrance fee,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 111920.0,
      "end_time": 114336.0,
      "text": "all he needs is the bouncer&#39;s account details.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 114360.0,
      "end_time": 115576.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 115600.0,
      "end_time": 117976.0,
      "text": "To criticize government spending:"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 118000.0,
      "end_time": 121576.0,
      "text": "[#ifafricawasabar South Africa would be ordering bottles it can&#39;t pronounce"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 121600.0,
      "end_time": 123455.0,
      "text": "running a tab it won&#39;t be able to pay]"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 123480.0,
      "end_time": 126560.0,
      "text": "To make light of geopolitical tensions:"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 126800.0,
      "end_time": 128455.0,
      "text": "[#IfAfricaWasABar South Sudan would be the new guy"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 128479.00000000001,
      "end_time": 130696.00000000001,
      "text": "with serious anger management issues.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 130720.0,
      "end_time": 132576.0,
      "text": "To remind us that even in Africa"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132600.0,
      "end_time": 135550.0,
      "text": "there are some countries we don&#39;t know exist:"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 135800.0,
      "end_time": 137456.0,
      "text": "[#IfAfricaWasABar Lesotho would be that person"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 137480.0,
      "end_time": 140495.0,
      "text": "who nobody really knows but is always in the pictures.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 140520.0,
      "end_time": 144776.0,
      "text": "And also to make fun of the countries that don&#39;t think that they&#39;re in Africa:"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 144800.0,
      "end_time": 147816.0,
      "text": "[#IfAfricaWasABar Egypt, Libya, Tunisia, Algeria and Morocco"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 147840.0,
      "end_time": 150560.0,
      "text": "be like \"What the hell are we doing here?!!\"]"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 150800.0,
      "end_time": 151976.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 152000.0,
      "end_time": 156960.0,
      "text": "And to note the countries that had made a big turnaround:"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 156120.0,
      "end_time": 158136.0,
      "text": "[#ifAfricawasabar Rwanda would be that girl"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 158160.0,
      "end_time": 161776.0,
      "text": "that comes with no money and no transport but leaves drunk, happy and rich]"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 161800.0,
      "end_time": 163480.0,
      "text": "But most importantly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 164360.0,
      "end_time": 167000.0,
      "text": "people were using the hashtag to connect."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 167640.0,
      "end_time": 170519.0,
      "text": "People were connecting over their Africanness."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171000.0,
      "end_time": 173296.0,
      "text": "So for one week in July,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 173320.0,
      "end_time": 177400.0,
      "text": "Twitter became a real African bar."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 177600.0,
      "end_time": 178976.0,
      "text": "And I was really thrilled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 179000.0,
      "end_time": 183360.0,
      "text": "mainly because I realized that Pan-Africanism could work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 184200.0,
      "end_time": 189495.0,
      "text": "that we had before us, between us, at our fingertips"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 189520.0,
      "end_time": 192976.0,
      "text": "a platform that just needed a small spark"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 193000.0,
      "end_time": 196400.0,
      "text": "to light in us a hunger for each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 197120.0,
      "end_time": 199296.0,
      "text": "My name is Siyanda Mohutsiwa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 199320.0,
      "end_time": 201550.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m 22 years old"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 201800.0,
      "end_time": 203400.0,
      "text": "and I am Pan-Africanist by birth."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 204160.0,
      "end_time": 206656.0,
      "text": "Now, I say I&#39;m Pan-Africanist by birth"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 206680.0,
      "end_time": 210560.0,
      "text": "because my parents are from two different African countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 210800.0,
      "end_time": 213816.0,
      "text": "My father&#39;s from a country called Botswana in southern Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 213840.0,
      "end_time": 216856.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s only slightly bigger than Germany."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 216880.0,
      "end_time": 220976.0,
      "text": "This year we celebrate our 50th year of stable democracy."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 221000.0,
      "end_time": 224576.0,
      "text": "And it has some very progressive social policies."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 224600.0,
      "end_time": 228616.0,
      "text": "My mother&#39;s country is the Kingdom of Swaziland."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 228640.0,
      "end_time": 231856.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a very, very small country, also in southern Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 231880.0,
      "end_time": 234960.0,
      "text": "It is Africa&#39;s last complete monarchy."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 235520.0,
      "end_time": 238336.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s been ruled by a king and a royal family"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 238360.0,
      "end_time": 239776.0,
      "text": "in line with their tradition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 239800.0,
      "end_time": 241120.0,
      "text": "for a very long time."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 241880.0,
      "end_time": 244856.0,
      "text": "On paper, these countries seem very different."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 244880.0,
      "end_time": 248416.0,
      "text": "And when I was a kid, I could see the difference."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 248440.0,
      "end_time": 252896.0,
      "text": "It rained a lot in one country, it didn&#39;t rain quite as much in the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 252920.0,
      "end_time": 255296.0,
      "text": "But outside of that, I didn&#39;t really realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 255320.0,
      "end_time": 259200.0,
      "text": "why it mattered that my parents were from two different places."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 259720.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263896.0,
      "text": "But it would go on to have a very peculiar effect on me."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 263920.0,
      "end_time": 266656.0,
      "text": "You see, I was born in one country"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 266680.0,
      "end_time": 268790.0,
      "text": "and raised in the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 268760.0,
      "end_time": 270656.0,
      "text": "When we moved to Botswana,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 270680.0,
      "end_time": 273616.0,
      "text": "I was a toddler who spoke fluent SiSwati"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 273640.0,
      "end_time": 275216.0,
      "text": "and nothing else."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 275240.0,
      "end_time": 277936.0,
      "text": "So I was being introduced to my new home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 277960.0,
      "end_time": 280215.0,
      "text": "my new cultural identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 280240.0,
      "end_time": 282256.0,
      "text": "as a complete outsider,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 282280.0,
      "end_time": 286535.0,
      "text": "incapable of comprehending anything that was being said to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 286560.0,
      "end_time": 290976.0,
      "text": "by the family and country whose traditions I was meant to move forward."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 291000.0,
      "end_time": 295216.0,
      "text": "But very soon, I would shed SiSwati."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 295240.0,
      "end_time": 297496.0,
      "text": "And when I would go back to Swaziland,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 297520.0,
      "end_time": 302120.0,
      "text": "I would be constantly confronted by how very non-Swazi I was becoming."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 302640.0,
      "end_time": 306496.0,
      "text": "Add to that my entry into Africa&#39;s private school system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 306520.0,
      "end_time": 310159.0,
      "text": "whose entire purpose is to beat the Africanness out of you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 310840.0,
      "end_time": 313679.0,
      "text": "and I would have a very peculiar adolescence."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 314240.0,
      "end_time": 320960.0,
      "text": "But I think that my interest in ideas of identity was born here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 320120.0,
      "end_time": 324376.0,
      "text": "in the strange intersection of belonging to two places at once"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 324400.0,
      "end_time": 327496.0,
      "text": "but not really belonging to either one very well"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 327520.0,
      "end_time": 332719.0,
      "text": "and belonging to this vast space in between and around simultaneously."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 333400.0,
      "end_time": 339760.0,
      "text": "I became obsessed with the idea of a shared African identity."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 340560.0,
      "end_time": 343336.0,
      "text": "Since then, I have continued to read about politics"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 343360.0,
      "end_time": 346776.0,
      "text": "and geography and identity and what all those things mean."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 346800.0,
      "end_time": 351536.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve also held on to a deep curiosity about African philosophies."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 351560.0,
      "end_time": 352816.0,
      "text": "When I began to read,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 352840.0,
      "end_time": 356256.0,
      "text": "I gravitated towards the works of black intellectuals"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 356280.0,
      "end_time": 358736.0,
      "text": "like Steve Biko and Frantz Fanon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 358760.0,
      "end_time": 360575.0,
      "text": "who tackled complex ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 360600.0,
      "end_time": 363656.0,
      "text": "like decolonization and black consciousness."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 363680.0,
      "end_time": 367896.0,
      "text": "And when I thought, at 14, that I had digested these grand ideas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 367920.0,
      "end_time": 371976.0,
      "text": "I moved on to the speeches of iconic African statesmen"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 372000.0,
      "end_time": 375160.0,
      "text": "like Burkina Faso&#39;s Thomas Sankara"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 375400.0,
      "end_time": 377456.0,
      "text": "and Congo&#39;s Patrice Lumumba."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 377480.0,
      "end_time": 381856.0,
      "text": "I read every piece of African fiction that I could get my hands on."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 381880.0,
      "end_time": 383536.0,
      "text": "So when Twitter came,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 383560.0,
      "end_time": 387736.0,
      "text": "I hopped on with the enthusiasm of a teenage girl"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 387760.0,
      "end_time": 393240.0,
      "text": "whose friends are super, super bored of hearing about all this random stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 394280.0,
      "end_time": 395616.0,
      "text": "The year was 2011"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 395640.0,
      "end_time": 398695.0,
      "text": "and all over southern Africa and the whole continent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 398720.0,
      "end_time": 402616.0,
      "text": "affordable data packages for smartphones and Internet surfing"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 402640.0,
      "end_time": 405455.0,
      "text": "became much easier to get."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 405480.0,
      "end_time": 410936.0,
      "text": "So my generation, we were sending messages to each other on this platform"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 410960.0,
      "end_time": 415416.0,
      "text": "that just needed 140 characters and a little bit of creativity."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 415440.0,
      "end_time": 417856.0,
      "text": "On long commutes to work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 417880.0,
      "end_time": 421336.0,
      "text": "in lectures that some of us should have been paying attention to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 421360.0,
      "end_time": 422936.0,
      "text": "on our lunch breaks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 422960.0,
      "end_time": 424976.0,
      "text": "we would communicate as much as we could"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 425000.0,
      "end_time": 428200.0,
      "text": "about the everyday realities of being young and African."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 428880.0,
      "end_time": 432376.0,
      "text": "But of course, this luxury was not available to everybody."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 432400.0,
      "end_time": 436960.0,
      "text": "So this meant that if you were a teenage girl in Botswana"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 436120.0,
      "end_time": 438176.0,
      "text": "and you wanted to have fun on the Internet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 438200.0,
      "end_time": 440856.0,
      "text": "one, you had to tweet in English."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 440880.0,
      "end_time": 445656.0,
      "text": "Two, you had to follow more than just the three other people you knew online."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 445680.0,
      "end_time": 450736.0,
      "text": "You had to follow South Africans, Zimbabweans, Ghanaians, Nigerians."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 450760.0,
      "end_time": 453536.0,
      "text": "And suddenly, your whole world opened up."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 453560.0,
      "end_time": 455896.0,
      "text": "And my whole world did open up."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 455920.0,
      "end_time": 459736.0,
      "text": "I followed vibrant Africans who were travelling around the continent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 459760.0,
      "end_time": 461216.0,
      "text": "taking pictures of themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 461240.0,
      "end_time": 464336.0,
      "text": "and posting them under the hashtag #myafrica."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 464360.0,
      "end_time": 465816.0,
      "text": "Because at that time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 465840.0,
      "end_time": 468895.0,
      "text": "if you were to search Africa on Twitter or on Google"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 468920.0,
      "end_time": 471176.0,
      "text": "or any kind of social media,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 471200.0,
      "end_time": 474976.0,
      "text": "you would think that the entire continent was just pictures of animals"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 475000.0,
      "end_time": 478496.0,
      "text": "and white guys drinking cocktails in hotel resorts."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 478520.0,
      "end_time": 480775.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 480800.0,
      "end_time": 483336.0,
      "text": "But Africans were using this platform"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 483360.0,
      "end_time": 487416.0,
      "text": "to take some kind of ownership of the tourism sectors."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 487440.0,
      "end_time": 491456.0,
      "text": "It was Africans taking selfies on the beaches of Nigeria."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 491480.0,
      "end_time": 494440.0,
      "text": "It was Africans in cocktail bars in Nairobi."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 495400.0,
      "end_time": 497517.0,
      "text": "And these were the same Africans that I began to meet"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 497541.0,
      "end_time": 499976.0,
      "text": "in my own travels around the continent."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 500000.0,
      "end_time": 504976.0,
      "text": "We would discuss African literature, politics, economic policy."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 505000.0,
      "end_time": 509136.0,
      "text": "But almost invariably, every single time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 509160.0,
      "end_time": 511520.0,
      "text": "we would end up discussing Twitter."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 512159.0,
      "end_time": 514600.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s when I realized what this was."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 515120.0,
      "end_time": 518416.0,
      "text": "We were standing in the middle of something amazing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 518440.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520736.00000000006,
      "text": "because for the first time ever"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 520760.0,
      "end_time": 525816.0,
      "text": "young Africans could discuss the future of our continent in real time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 525840.0,
      "end_time": 530240.0,
      "text": "without the restriction of borders, finances and watchful governments."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 530720.0,
      "end_time": 532655.0,
      "text": "Because the little known truth is"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 532679.0,
      "end_time": 536536.0,
      "text": "many Africans know a lot less about other African countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 536560.0,
      "end_time": 539640.0,
      "text": "than some Westerners might know about Africa as a whole."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 540160.0,
      "end_time": 541736.0,
      "text": "This is by accident,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 541760.0,
      "end_time": 543896.0,
      "text": "but sometimes, it&#39;s by design."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 543920.0,
      "end_time": 546856.0,
      "text": "For example, in apartheid South Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 546880.0,
      "end_time": 550376.0,
      "text": "black South Africans were constantly being bombarded"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 550400.0,
      "end_time": 553496.0,
      "text": "with this message that any country ruled by black people"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 553520.0,
      "end_time": 555496.0,
      "text": "was destined for failure."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 555520.0,
      "end_time": 558550.0,
      "text": "And this was done to convince them"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 558800.0,
      "end_time": 561736.0,
      "text": "that they were much better off under crushing white rule"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 561760.0,
      "end_time": 565120.0,
      "text": "than they were living in a black and free nation."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 565640.0,
      "end_time": 570856.0,
      "text": "Add to that Africa&#39;s colonial, archaic education system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 570880.0,
      "end_time": 574856.0,
      "text": "which has been unthinkingly carried over from the 1920s --"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 574880.0,
      "end_time": 579176.0,
      "text": "and at the age of 15, I could name all the various causes"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 579200.0,
      "end_time": 583256.0,
      "text": "of the wars that had happened in Europe in the past 200 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 583280.0,
      "end_time": 586120.0,
      "text": "but I couldn&#39;t name the president of my neighboring country."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 586640.0,
      "end_time": 589496.0,
      "text": "And to me, this doesn&#39;t make any sense"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 589520.0,
      "end_time": 591536.0,
      "text": "because whether we like it or not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 591560.0,
      "end_time": 595199.0,
      "text": "the fates of African people are deeply intertwined."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 595680.0,
      "end_time": 599175.0,
      "text": "When disaster hits, when turmoil hits,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 599200.0,
      "end_time": 601336.0,
      "text": "we share the consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 601360.0,
      "end_time": 604336.0,
      "text": "When Burundians flee political turmoil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 604360.0,
      "end_time": 605696.0,
      "text": "they go to us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 605720.0,
      "end_time": 607736.0,
      "text": "to other African countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 607760.0,
      "end_time": 611520.0,
      "text": "Africa has six of the world&#39;s largest refugee centers."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 612320.0,
      "end_time": 614976.0,
      "text": "What was once a Burundian problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 615000.0,
      "end_time": 617160.0,
      "text": "becomes an African problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 617400.0,
      "end_time": 620616.0,
      "text": "So to me, there are no Sudanese problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 620640.0,
      "end_time": 623560.0,
      "text": "or South African problems or Kenyan problems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 623800.0,
      "end_time": 624656.0,
      "text": "only African problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 624680.0,
      "end_time": 627000.0,
      "text": "because eventually, we share the turmoil."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 627600.0,
      "end_time": 629336.0,
      "text": "So if we share the problems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 629360.0,
      "end_time": 632600.0,
      "text": "why aren&#39;t we doing a better job of sharing the successes?"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 633200.0,
      "end_time": 634416.0,
      "text": "How can we do that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 634440.0,
      "end_time": 635696.0,
      "text": "Well, in the long term,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 635720.0,
      "end_time": 638576.0,
      "text": "we can shoot towards increasing inter-African trade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 638600.0,
      "end_time": 641136.0,
      "text": "removing borders and putting pressure on leaders"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 641160.0,
      "end_time": 644560.0,
      "text": "to fulfill regional agreements they&#39;ve already signed."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 645200.0,
      "end_time": 650336.0,
      "text": "But I think that the biggest way for Africa to share its successes"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 650360.0,
      "end_time": 654800.0,
      "text": "is to foster something I like to call social Pan-Africanism."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 655320.0,
      "end_time": 658176.0,
      "text": "Now, political Pan-Africanism already exists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 658200.0,
      "end_time": 660800.0,
      "text": "so I&#39;m not inventing anything totally new here."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 661360.0,
      "end_time": 662936.0,
      "text": "But political Pan-Africanism"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 662960.0,
      "end_time": 666496.0,
      "text": "is usually the African unity of the political elite."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 666520.0,
      "end_time": 667856.0,
      "text": "And who does that benefit?"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 667880.0,
      "end_time": 670640.0,
      "text": "Well, African leaders, almost exclusively."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 671280.0,
      "end_time": 674175.0,
      "text": "No, what I&#39;m talking about"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 674200.0,
      "end_time": 677280.0,
      "text": "is the Pan-Africanism of the ordinary African."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 677840.0,
      "end_time": 679896.0,
      "text": "Young Africans like me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 679920.0,
      "end_time": 682896.0,
      "text": "we are bursting with creative energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 682920.0,
      "end_time": 685415.0,
      "text": "with innovative ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 685440.0,
      "end_time": 688816.0,
      "text": "But with bad governance and shaky institutions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 688840.0,
      "end_time": 691496.0,
      "text": "all of this potential could go to waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 691520.0,
      "end_time": 694550.0,
      "text": "On a continent where more than a handful of leaders"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 694800.0,
      "end_time": 695936.0,
      "text": "have been in power longer"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 695960.0,
      "end_time": 699360.0,
      "text": "than the majority of the populations has been alive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 700360.0,
      "end_time": 703160.0,
      "text": "we are in desperate need of something new,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 703760.0,
      "end_time": 705480.0,
      "text": "something that works."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 706000.0,
      "end_time": 710960.0,
      "text": "And I think that thing is social Pan-Africanism."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 711560.0,
      "end_time": 714695.0,
      "text": "My dream is that young Africans"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 714720.0,
      "end_time": 720256.0,
      "text": "stop allowing borders and circumstance to suffocate our innovation."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 720280.0,
      "end_time": 724616.0,
      "text": "My dream is that when a young African comes up with something brilliant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 724640.0,
      "end_time": 728560.0,
      "text": "they don&#39;t say, \"Well, this wouldn&#39;t work in my country,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 728800.0,
      "end_time": 729496.0,
      "text": "and then give up."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 729520.0,
      "end_time": 733175.0,
      "text": "My dream is that young Africans begin to realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 733200.0,
      "end_time": 737520.0,
      "text": "that the entire continent is our canvas, is our home."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 738920.0,
      "end_time": 743256.0,
      "text": "Using the Internet, we can begin to think collaboratively,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 743280.0,
      "end_time": 745856.0,
      "text": "we can begin to innovate together."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 745880.0,
      "end_time": 749456.0,
      "text": "In Africa, we say, \"If you want to go fast, you go alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 749480.0,
      "end_time": 752336.0,
      "text": "but if you want to go far, you go together.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 752360.0,
      "end_time": 758120.0,
      "text": "And I believe that social Pan-Africanism is how we can go far together."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 759480.0,
      "end_time": 761496.0,
      "text": "And this is already happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 761520.0,
      "end_time": 764496.0,
      "text": "Access to these online networks has given young Africans"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 764520.0,
      "end_time": 768896.0,
      "text": "something we&#39;ve always had to violently take: a voice."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 768920.0,
      "end_time": 770815.0,
      "text": "We now have a platform."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 770840.0,
      "end_time": 774776.0,
      "text": "Before now, if you wanted to hear from the youth in Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 774800.0,
      "end_time": 778536.0,
      "text": "you waited for the 65-year-old minister of youth --"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 778560.0,
      "end_time": 779856.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 779880.0,
      "end_time": 781400.0,
      "text": "to wake up in the morning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 781960.0,
      "end_time": 784400.0,
      "text": "take his heartburn medication"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 785360.0,
      "end_time": 788256.0,
      "text": "and then tell you the plans he has for your generation"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 788280.0,
      "end_time": 789760.0,
      "text": "in 20 years time."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 790400.0,
      "end_time": 796336.0,
      "text": "Before now, if you wanted to be heard by your possibly tyrannical government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 796360.0,
      "end_time": 799736.0,
      "text": "you were pushed to protest, suffer the consequences"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 799760.0,
      "end_time": 801415.0,
      "text": "and have your fingers crossed"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 801440.0,
      "end_time": 804960.0,
      "text": "that some Western paper somewhere might make someone care."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 805560.0,
      "end_time": 808376.0,
      "text": "But now we have opportunities to back each other up"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 808400.0,
      "end_time": 810616.0,
      "text": "in ways we never could before."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 810640.0,
      "end_time": 812376.0,
      "text": "We support South African students"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 812400.0,
      "end_time": 816160.0,
      "text": "who are marching against ridiculously high tertiary fees."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 816400.0,
      "end_time": 819376.0,
      "text": "We support Zimbabwean women who are marching to parliament."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 819400.0,
      "end_time": 822840.0,
      "text": "We support Angolan journalists who are being illegally detained."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 823560.0,
      "end_time": 825695.0,
      "text": "For the first time ever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 825720.0,
      "end_time": 830176.0,
      "text": "African pain and African aspiration"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 830200.0,
      "end_time": 833496.0,
      "text": "has the ability to be witnessed"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 833520.0,
      "end_time": 837136.0,
      "text": "by those who can empathize with it the most:"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 837160.0,
      "end_time": 838439.0,
      "text": "other Africans."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 838920.0,
      "end_time": 842856.0,
      "text": "I believe that with a social Pan-Africanist thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 842880.0,
      "end_time": 844920.0,
      "text": "and using the Internet as a tool,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 845920.0,
      "end_time": 848776.0,
      "text": "we can begin to rescue each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 848800.0,
      "end_time": 852376.0,
      "text": "and ultimately, to rescue ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 852400.0,
      "end_time": 853616.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 853640.0,
      "end_time": 861548.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}